    <question>
        <prompt>Robert La Follette's Progressive Party campaign in 1924:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Won the presidential election</option>
            <option letter="b">Challenged conservative Republican policies</option>
            <option letter="c">Supported business interests</option>
            <option letter="d">Promoted prohibition</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>Robert La Follette's 1924 Progressive Party campaign challenged the conservative policies of the Republican Party. His platform called for public ownership of water power and railroads, stronger labor rights, farm relief, and opposition to monopolies. Though he received nearly 5 million votes, the campaign highlighted the declining influence of progressivism in 1920s America as conservative Republican Calvin Coolidge won easily.</explanation>
